#: ../../howtos/company.rst:34
msgid "Company-dependent fields"
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:36
msgid ""
"When a record is available from multiple companies, we must expect that "
"different values will be assigned to a given field depending on the "
"company from which the value is set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:39
msgid ""
"For the field of a same record to support several values, it must be "
"defined with the attribute `company_dependent` set to `True`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:58
msgid ""
"The `_compute_display_info` method is decorated with "
"`depends_context('force_company')` (see "
":attr:`~odoo.api.depends_context`) to ensure that the computed field is "
"recomputed depending on the forced/current company (`force_company` "
"context key set, or `self.env.company`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:63
msgid ""
"When a company-dependent field is read, the current company is used to "
"retrieve its value. In other words, if a user is logged in companies A "
"and B with A as main company and creates a record for company B, the "
"values of company-dependent fields will be that of company A."
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:67
msgid ""
"To read the values of company-dependent fields set from another company "
"than the current one, the context key `force_company` must be set to the "
"ID of the desired company."
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:82
msgid "Multi-company consistency"
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:84
msgid ""
"When a record is made shareable between several companies by the mean of "
"a `company_id` field, we must take care that it cannot be linked to the "
"record of another company through a relational field. For instance, we do"
" not want to have a sales order and its invoice belonging to different "
"companies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:88
msgid "To ensure this multi-company consistency, you must:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:90
msgid "Set the class attribute `_check_company_auto` to `True`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:91
msgid ""
"Define relational fields with the attribute `check_company` set to `True`"
" if their model has a `company_id` field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:94
msgid ""
"On each :meth:`~odoo.models.Model.create` and "
":meth:`~odoo.models.Model.write`, automatic checks will be triggered to "
"ensure the multi-company consistency of the record."
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:108
msgid "The field `company_id` must not be defined with `check_company=True`."
msgstr ""

