#: odoo.models.Model._check_company:8 of
msgid ""
"For :class:`~odoo.addons.base.models.res_users` relational fields, "
"verifies record company is in `company_ids` fields."
msgstr ""

#: odoo.models.Model._check_company:11 of
msgid ""
"User with main company A, having access to company A and B, could be "
"assigned or linked to records in company B."
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:113
msgid ""
"The `check_company` feature performs a strict check ! It means that if a "
"record has no `company_id` (i.e. the field is not required), it cannot be"
" linked to a record whose `company_id` is set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:119
msgid ""
"When no domain is defined on the field and `check_company` is set to "
"`True`, a default domain is added: `['|', '('company_id', '=', False), "
"('company_id', '=', company_id)]`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:125
msgid "Default company"
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:127
msgid ""
"When the field `company_id` is made required on a model, a good practice "
"is to set a default company. It eases the setup flow for the user or even"
" guarantees its validity when the company is hidden from the view. "
"Indeed, the company is usually hidden if the user does not have access to"
" multiple companies (i.e. when the user does not have the group "
"`base.group_multi_company`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:149
msgid "Views"
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:151
msgid ""
"As stated in :ref:`above <howto/company/default_company>`, the company is"
" usually hidden from the view if the user does not have access to "
"multiple companies. This is tested with the group "
"`base.group_multi_company`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:178
msgid "Security rules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:180
msgid ""
"When working with records shared across companies or restricted to a "
"single company, we must take care that a user does not have access to "
"records belonging to other companies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../howtos/company.rst:183
msgid ""
"This is achieved with security rules based on `company_ids`, which "
"contains the current companies of the user (the companies the user "
"checked in the multi-company widget)."
msgstr ""

